Go to terraform-multiple-env repository like git clone https://github.com/hareesh-reddy-g/terraform-multiple-env.git 
then 
** cd tfvars 

** terraform init -backend-config=dev/backend.tf

** terraform plan -var-file=dev/dev.tfvars

** terraform apply -auto-approve -var-file=dev/dev.tfvars



upto here dev work instance and everything created noww we have to change to production environment

** terraform init -backend-config=prod/backend.tf -reconfigure

** terraform plan -var-file=prod/prod.tfvars

** terraform apply -auto-approve -var-file=prod/prod.tfvars


If we want to destroy development what i have to do means follow this
** terraform init -backend-config=dev/backend.tf -reconfigure
** terraform destroy -auto-approve -var-file=dev/dev.tfvars


**  terraform workspace

** terraform workspace list 

** terraform workspace new dev

** terraform workspace new prod 

** terraform workspace list 

** terraform workspace select dev

** terraform workspace list 

** cd ..
** cd workspaces

** terraform workspace create dev

** terraform workspace new dev 

** cd ..

** cd tfvars

** terraform init -backend-config=prod/backend.tf -reconfigure

** terraform destroy -var-file=prod/prod.tfvars

** terraform init 

** terraform plan

** terraform apply -auto-approve





